  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally involves financial transactions designed to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money. The specific legal definition can vary between jurisdictions, but typically involves three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Conducting complex transactions to obscure the money's origin\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economic activities\n\nMost legal definitions require:\n- Knowingly processing funds from criminal activity\n- Attempting to disguise the source of illegal funds\n- Intentionally conducting financial transactions to hide criminal proceeds\n\nSpecific requirements and penalties differ by country and jurisdiction. Would you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
